FBIS3-53543 "drnes011_j_94010" FBIS-NES-94-011 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Jan 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Saudi Arabia Fahd Meets Pakistani President BK1701113694 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in English 1100 GMT 17 Jan 94 BK1701113694 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] President Sardar Farooq Ahmad Khan Leghari and the Saudi King, Fahd Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz, have made a passionate appeal to the Afghan leaders to establish and maintain peace in their country. In a joint appeal during a meeting in Riyadh last night, the two leaders urged the Afghan factions to end the conflict in true of spirit of Islamic teachings. The two sides held wide-ranging talks covering regional and world issues of mutual interest and bilateral cooperation. The president flew into Jeddah this morning.
